The next Biennial should be held at Ronchi Boukou in Kassel; 
“The Italian Biennale is a collective effort, a project of a group of artists and cultural producers,” said Bernardo De Vita, the head of the Bettina DiPiazza Foundation. “The biennial should reflect the great diversity of artistic traditions, from the classical to the modern and from the ancient to the contemporary. It should be an open canvas for artists of all ages and all places.”According to De Vitam, the upcoming event’s theme “Isolation” will center around the idea that art can be the only source of inspiration for the individual and the group. "The theme of isolation will be the theme of the exhibition,” said De Vitam. “This is the only way to give a sense of belonging to a place, that is in tune with what is going on here.”


